    "html": "<section class=\"problem\" id=\"5-31\"><h2>5-31</h2><div class=\"tagline\"><span class=\"pill\">Lesson</span> Sorted to Unit 7, Section 4: Comparing Function Families</div><div class=\"audit\">Audit note: Compares linear rebound-height modeling to exponential successive-bounce modeling.</div>\n<div class=\"contentContainerReference-body\"><p class=\"\" style=\"\">Compare your graph for the height of successive bounces in problem <span class=\"bookSpecificContent\" data-book-id=\"77c6bab0-733e-11e9-be9b-611c324990be\">5-29</span> to the graph for drop height versus bounce height that you investigated in Lesson <span class=\"bookSpecificContent\" data-book-id=\"77c6bab0-733e-11e9-be9b-611c324990be\">5.1.2</span>. \t</p><ol class=\"lower-alpha\" type=\"a\"><li><p class=\"\" style=\"\">Can you use the same kind of equation to model the two situations? That is, what family of functions do you think would make the best fit for each data set? Discuss this with your team and be ready to report and justify your choice.</p></li><li><p class=\"\" style=\"\">Describe how the pattern of growth for successive bounces is the same as or different from other models that you have looked at previously.</p></li></ol></div><div class=\"graph-workspace\"></div><div class=\"workspace workspace-lg\"></div>\n</section>",
